<CSSBorder-image>
<summary>
The <strong><c>border-image</c></strong> <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS">CSS</see> property draws an image around a given element. It replaces the element&amp;apos;s regular <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border">border</see>.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>EmbedInteractiveExample("pages/css/border-image.html")</para><blockquote class="NOTE"><h5>NOTE</h5><para><strong>Note:</strong> You should specify a separate <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border-style">border-style</see> in case the border image fails to load. Although the specification doesn't strictly require it, some browsers don't render the border image if <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border-style">border-style</see> is <c>none</c> or <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border-width">border-width</see> is <c>0</c>.</para></blockquote>
